cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CC, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of physical-layer network coding and its asymptotic gain using information-theoretic tools. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on designing network coding schemes and studying their performance/complexity tradeoffs. 
3. cs.SI (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the use of module theory in developing a framework for studying network coding schemes. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the decoding complexity of the designed network coding schemes. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the use of lattice-reduction-based algorithms in decoding multiple linear combinations.
